description:
GenAI has pushed the boundaries of what's possible and is poised to revolutionise the workplace and other aspects of society. The AI hype has driven inflated valuations, sparked government initiatives for regional AI hubs, and spurred significant investment in startups, all contributing to global economic growth. While businesses are eagerly exploring GenAI for competitive advantages, its potential to reshape society - for better or worse - is equally profound. GenAI could empower individuals and uplift communities, yet it also risks widening existing inequalities. What unexpected social consequences has the GenAI wave already unleashed? How can the risks of AI be addressed while ensuring that its development and deployment are equitable and just?
